<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 01 at 5:14PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of eastern Armstrong,
southern Gray and Donley Counties through 545 PM CDT...
At 514 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles northwest of Lake Mcclellan to 9 miles
southeast of Goodnight to 5 miles southeast of Tulia. Movement was
southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and blowing dust.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Clarendon, Mclean, Howardwick, Hedley, Lelia Lake, Lake Mcclellan,
Alanreed and Greenbelt Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Do not drive into areas where blowing dust restricts visibility.</instruction>
